direction: right

*.style.border-radius: 8
*.style.font-size: 13
*.style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
*.style.stroke: "#333333"

# --- Entry / Orchestrator ---

strat-security-review: |md
  **/strat-security-review**

  - fetch STRAT from Jira, check idempotency
  - determine review tier (light/standard/deep)
  - extract threat surface inventory mechanically
  - spawn 3 independent reviewers (parallel, isolated)
  - synthesize consensus with confidence tagging
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Sub-agent (forked context, x3) ---

security-reviewer: |md
  **security-reviewer**
  LLM sub-agent (x3, forked)

  - check 39 risk patterns against threat surface
  - creative exploration for novel attack surfaces
  - apply relevance gate (STRAT evidence required)
  - classify severity via decision tree
  - check RHOAI organizational constraints
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

# --- External: Jira ---

jira: |md
  **Jira**
  (RHAISTRAT)
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}

# --- Output ---

output: |md
  **Output**

  - security-review.md (full consensus)
  - security-requirements.md (attached to Jira)
  - verdict label: pass / concerns / fail
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Edges ---

jira -> strat-security-review: "STRAT content"
strat-security-review -> security-reviewer: "threat-surface.md\n+ tier + STRAT key"
security-reviewer -> strat-security-review: "reviewer-N.md (x3)"
strat-security-review -> output: "consensus verdict"
output -> jira: "attach requirements\n+ verdict label" {
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
